version:
Verilator 5.025 devel rev v5.024-56-g5f85c8942

Please find attached a test in test_regress format.

[t_type_match.zip](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/15370455/t_type_match.zip)


Type used for __Vtrigprevexpr (in generated C++ code) do not match the type used for the signal itself

VL_IN8(c[1],0,0); // CData [1]

VlUnpacked<CData/*0:0*/, 1> __Vtrigprevexpr___TOP__t__DOT__i_top__DOT__i_unit__c__1;


And following operations fail to compile:

vlSelf->__VactTriggered.set(0U, vlSymsp->TOP__t__DOT__i_top__DOT__i_unit.c.neq(vlSelf->__Vtrigprevexpr___TOP__t__DOT__i_top__DOT__i_unit__c__1));

Vt_type_match___024root__DepSet_hb7a96300__0.cpp:18:80: error: request for member 'neq' in '((Vt_type_match__Syms* __restrict__)vlSymsp)->Vt_type_match__Syms::TOP__t__DOT__i_top__DOT__i_unit.Vt_type_match_unit::c', which is of non-class type 'CData [1]' {aka 'unsigned char [1]'}
     vlSelf->__VactTriggered.set(0U, vlSymsp->TOP__t__DOT__i_top__DOT__i_unit.c.neq(vlSelf->__Vtrigprevexpr___TOP__t__DOT__i_top__DOT__i_unit__c__1));



vlSelf->__Vtrigprevexpr___TOP__t__DOT__i_top__DOT__i_unit__c__1.assign(vlSymsp->TOP__t__DOT__i_top__DOT__i_unit.c);

In file included from Vt_type_match__ALL.cpp:4:
Vt_type_match___024root__DepSet_hb7a96300__0.cpp:21:118: error: no matching function for call to 'VlUnpacked<unsigned char, 1>::assign(CData [1])'
     vlSelf->__Vtrigprevexpr___TOP__t__DOT__i_top__DOT__i_unit__c__1.assign(vlSymsp->TOP__t__DOT__i_top__DOT__i_unit.c);

Thanks,
Pawel
